miniPy
======

miniPy is a small educational language and prototype compiler implemented in Python.
The project provides two backends:

- Transpiler â†’ CPython AST: converts miniPy programs to Python ast.Module, compiles, and executes them.
- Interpreter: an AST-walking interpreter backend useful for testing and debugging language semantics.

Core features implemented:
- Indentation-based blocks (INDENT / DEDENT)
- Assignments, expressions, arithmetic and comparison operators
- If / elif / else, while loops
- Function definitions, calls, recursion, lexical closures, return
- String literals and concatenation
- Basic semantic checking (undeclared variable detection)
- Two execution backends and example programs

For more details and usage examples, see README.md in the project root.